com.poesys.db.dto

Class AbstractCollectionReadSetter<T extends IDbDto>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractSetter<T>
      • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractCollectionReadSetter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of IDbDto to query
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISet, java.io.Serializable

    public abstract class AbstractCollectionReadSetter<T extends IDbDto>
extends AbstractSetter<T>
implements ISet
    An abstract implementation of the ISet interface for a Strategy-pattern class that sets a collection element of a data transfer object as part of a de-serialization read-object process. The abstract methods parameterize the class with objects that the set() method uses in processing the query. The class that implements a concrete subclass of this setter implementation calls the set(Connection) method, which queries the objects and then calls the set(Collection) method to update the internal collection. The class accesses a list of primary keys for T objects and queries them individually using a query-by-key DAO. The query-by-key process will look in any cache implemented for the DTO and will retrieve the object from the cache if it's there, or it will query the object from the database if it isn't cached.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller
